# ISSAC build conventions

Authoritative spec: DEVELOPMENT.md at the repo root. Follow its schema, file
structure and milestones. Implement ONE milestone per session.

## Stack
- PHP 8.1+, PSR-12. Namespace `Issac\`, PSR-4 from `plugins/issac-assessment/src/`.
- WordPress + ACF Pro + mPDF (Composer). No form plugins (NinjaForms etc.) — ever.

## Data boundaries (critical)
- Instrument content (domains, subsections, items, descriptors) lives in the CPTs
  `issac_domain`, `issac_subsection`, `issac_item` with ACF fields. Read it ONLY
  through the cached `InstrumentRepository` — never scatter `get_field()` calls.
- Transactional data (assessments, responses, events) lives ONLY in the custom
  tables `wp_issac_*`. Never store interactions in `wp_posts`/`wp_postmeta`.
- Responses reference the stable `item_code` ("1.1".."5.18"), never post IDs.
- Totals/percentages are always computed live from the instrument tree — never hard-coded.
- Items use an `is_active` toggle; never hard-delete content that has responses.

## Security (non-negotiable)
- All SQL through `$wpdb->prepare()`; cast ints with `absint()`.
- Every REST route under `issac/v1` has a `permission_callback` and requires the
  nonce. Resolve the user's assessment from `get_current_user_id()`, never from input.
- Escape all output: `esc_html` / `esc_attr` / `wp_kses_post`.
- Validate score is 1–5 server-side; validate `item_code` exists and is active.

## ACF & content integrity
- Field groups live in `acf-json/` (Local JSON), committed to Git.
- NEVER regenerate ISSAC question/descriptor text from memory. Content comes only
  from the import JSON (extracted from the source DOCX) or from wp-admin edits.

## Scoring
- Keep `ScoringService` pure PHP (no WP functions) so it can be unit-tested.